to download splunk:

go to splunk.com ---> create an account ----> download with wgwt command or download in your pc later on transfer the package with winscp

wget -O splunk-8.2.4-87e2dda940d1-Linux-x86_64.tgz 'https://download.splunk.com/products/splunk/releases/8.2.4/linux/splunk-8.2.4-87e2dda940d1-Linux-x86_64.tgz'

go to the directory where you want to install splunk. the installation package should be there.
.....
tar xvfz splunkforwarder-8.2.4-87e2dda940d1-Linux-s390x.tgz
for 1st time accept license.

#SPLUNK_HOME/bin/
./splunk start --accept-license

to run splunk at start up
cd #SPLUNK_HOME/bin/
./splunk enable boot-start


#SPLUNK_HOME/bin/splunk start | stop | status
